,Not Recommended,299250,29615238,Posted: 31 January,all,DeadPoolX,"PROS:+ You can control different types of civilian vessels, from small tugboats to huge cruise liners+ You can walk around your ship in first-person mode+ A wide variety of missions are available+ A mission editor is included so you can design your own routes and objectivesCONS:- Options menu is bare bones (three non-descript settings for graphics and an audio slider that controls both sound and music at the same time)- Graphics are on the low end and except for the odd suicidal AI-controlled ship, the entire world seems lifeless- Music is incredibly annoying- Physics and handling of ships feels a little off- No freeplay or sandbox mode, just scripted missions (unless you use the mission editor)- The mission editor is overly complex and very unintuitive- AI-controlled ships won't adjust their course, so if you happen to be in the way (even if this means you're simply docked), they will ram you- Crashes to the desktop so often it's unlikely you'll ever play through an entire mission without losing all of your progress at least onceVERDICT: As much as I wanted to like ESS, I just couldn't. Even if I could forgive some of this game's faults, the constant crashes and restrictive gameplay are just too much. Unless you find this game as part of a package deal (on Humble Bundle, for instance) or at an extremely low price, I'd have to say ""No, don't buy this game."""
