,Recommended,299250,14851677,"Posted: 12 March, 2015",all,ukandywest,"I was a little bit apprehensive about the game, having read mixed reviews here.  Anyway I bit the bullet and am very pleased.  I have a fairly average PC, but it has still allowed me to crank the graphics right up.  Admittedly, there was some chop in early 'missions' immediately after installation, however, a full defrag and restart cured that.I work in the commercial shipping industry, and quite enjoy this game.  As far as ""simulation"" goes, it is a nice simplified ship driving game without too much depth that I use to kill time.  Do not expect procedural realism, but you will get a genuine appreciation for the techniques required to move the included vessels around in their daily work.If you are wondering about your PC specs, I have an AMD A10 processor, 8GB DDR3 and an ATI R9270 and it works perfectly with room for more.  The difference between the LOW and HIGH graphics options in-game isn't huge either so most modern PCs should run it with nice visuals."
