76561198099452767,Not Recommended,299250,14568759,"Posted: 20 February, 2015",all,tmparro,"European Ship Simulator Review.So before I get started on this review I wanted to say that this is my opinion of the game. Please watch videos of this game on youtube before buying this game. Do your resach and don't make the mistake I did__________________________________________________________________________________Main PromblomThis game claims to be a ship simulater, which it is. This game also claims to be an open world game. Which it is not. This game is a simulator that allows you to spawn in a ship and procced from point A to point B. This is not open world. To me open world is when you can spawn and go any where you want. In this game you can NOT do that. Another thing I wanted to say is this game has been out for about 3 years. Anther game I play and love called Unturned is also 3 years. (just had its 3 year anniversery) Untunred was developed by 1 person. While this game was developed by an entire company! Unturned is still updating to this day. Infact a HUGE update for that game was just released that adds a new map and a heck load of content. ESS stoped updating after a few months of World Ship Simulator was released the same day and year of Euro Ship Simulator was. Keep in mind 1 person managed to keep a game alive for 3 years while an entire company can't even release a bug fix update.__________________________________________________________________________________Pro's- A few missions that you can do with varents of ships/boats.- Has a mission editer ( I'm to stupid to figure it out ).- Desent water graphics but not great.- Working AI__________________________________________________________________________________Cons- Speed boat has VARY VARY VARY sensitive turning.- No open world as the store page catagories says it does have open world.- Mission editer to complacated for some people. ( Including me )- Game stopped updateing at an early stage of development. Suprised it came out of early access.- Lack of ship interior. From what I seen in Ship Simulator Extreames you can explore almost the entire ship you selected. While in this game you can only walk around the navagation bridge.- Ship horns sound nothing like they should. A week before this review I went on a cruise. Before the ship leaves port the ship horn honks 3 times. The horn sounded loud and low pitched. I also heard many other cruise ship horns in my life time and they sound loud and mighty. In this game ESS the cruise ship horn sounds like a loud car horn.- Bad frame rate from time to time. I have a desent gameing computer and can run many games well. I have every thing reqiured to run this game properly. All though I still have bad frame rate even when my game is on the lowest settings.__________________________________________________________________________________Whats left to say about this game?This game is a huge disappointment because of the cons. It claimed to have open world and it didn't. All the cons also make this game a disapointment. Do not buy this game unless your sure you want it.Would I recommend this game?No, I would not recommend this game at all.What game would you recommend thats related to this?I would recommend Ship Simulator Extreams. From what I seen SSE is a good ship simulator that has every thing that this game doesn't. I have not played this myself but plain onto soon.__________________________________________________________________________________If you have read this review thank you for your time to read this. I hope you make the choice thats right to you what ever that choice may be."
